The paper deals with a distributed algorithm for matrix rank estimation, which involves communication complexity and information theory (cs.IT) aspects. The algorithm proposed is randomized, which suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and randomized algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses lower bounds on communication complexity, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and theoretical computer science (cs.THE). Finally, the numerical experiments suggest a practical application of the algorithm, which could fall under scientific computing (cs.NA) or systems and control (cs.SY).
